      "content": "# Spot Bitcoin ETFs Add $458M as IBIT Leads Inflows. * U.S. spot bitcoin ETFs recorded $458.2 million in net inflows on Monday, with no funds posting outflows. Spot Bitcoin ETFs Add $458M as IBIT Leads Inflows. U.S. spot bitcoin exchange-traded funds took in $458.2 million of net inflows on Monday as institutions bought into bitcoin’s recent correction. The move was led by $263.2 million into BlackRock’s IBIT, while seven other funds including Fidelity and Grayscale also recorded inflows, and none posted outflows, according to SoSoValue. > “The positive spot bitcoin ETF inflows mark a turning point as major allocators appear to view current price levels as an attractive entry point amid bitcoin’s recent correction and stabilization.”. For daily tracking of U.S. spot ETF activity, ETF flows data shows net inflows and outflows in USD and BTC, alongside broader U.S. ETF holdings. Spot Bitcoin ETFs Add $458M as IBIT Leads Inflows. Spot Bitcoin ETFs Add $458M as IBIT Leads Inflows.",
