      "url": "https://bitbo.io/news/bitcoin-etfs-inflows-366-million/",
      "content": "$366M Flow Into Bitcoin ETFs as BTC Surpasses $65K $366M Flow Into Bitcoin ETFs as BTC Surpasses $65K Bitcoin surged past $65,000, driving $366 million into U.S. Bitcoin ETFs on Sept. 26, the largest inflows in over two months. ### Key Takeaways * Bitcoin ETFs saw $366M in inflows as BTC surged above $65K. * ARK 21Shares and BlackRock led ETF inflows, collecting $113.8M and $93.4M, respectively. * The Grayscale Bitcoin Trust saw a $7.7M outflow, totaling $20.1B in losses since January. Bitcoin saw a significant boost on Sept. 26, pushing above $65,000 and bringing in $365.7 million to U.S. spot Bitcoin ETFs. This marked the highest daily inflow for Bitcoin ETFs in over two months, according to data from Farside Investors. The ARK 21Shares Bitcoin ETF led with $113.8 million in inflows, followed by BlackRock iShares Bitcoin Trust with $93.4 million. The Fidelity Wise Origin Bitcoin Fund also saw significant interest, pulling in $74 million. In contrast, the Grayscale Bitcoin Trust continued to face outflows, losing $7.7 million on the day, bringing its total outflows to $20.1 billion since becoming a spot ETF in January. Since the inception of all 11 U.S.-listed spot Bitcoin ETFs, the total inflow has reached $18.3 billion. Nate Geraci, president of ETF Store, noted on X: > Out of 500 ETFs launched in 2024, less than 25 have taken this amount in for the _entire year_. While Bitcoin ETFs have seen strong inflows, spot Ethereum ETFs lag behind. On the same day, nine Ethereum ETFs registered outflows of $100,000, with Grayscale’s Ethereum Trust continuing to bleed assets, losing $36 million on Sept. ### Get more news like this Twice-weekly Bitcoin-only newsletter by Bitbo. ### Indian Politician Calls for Bitcoin Reserve Pilot ### GameStop Shares Flat After $450M Raise, Bitcoin Rumors ### Metaplanet Surpasses Tesla With 12,345 Bitcoin Holdings Bitcoin Mine Proposal in Minnesota Halted Over Noise Concerns Gensler Reaffirms Bitcoin Isn’t a Security, Dodges Trump Question Bitbo News brings you Bitcoin news that matters.",
