    {
      "title": "Bitcoin ETFs See Biggest Inflow Day in Three Weeks",
      "url": "https://bitbo.io/news/bitcoin-etfs-inflows-rebound",
      "content": "# Bitcoin ETFs See Biggest Inflow Day in Three Weeks. * U.S. spot Bitcoin ETFs recorded $506.5 million of net inflows, the highest day in three weeks. * BlackRock's IBIT led with $297.4 million, and no fund posted outflows on the day. * The move followed five straight weeks of ETF net outflows through Feb. 20 totaling more than $3.8 billion. Bitcoin ETFs See Biggest Inflow Day in Three Weeks. U.S. spot Bitcoin exchange-traded funds posted their largest single-day net inflows in three weeks on Wednesday, pulling in $506.5 million. BlackRock’s IBIT led the group with $297.4 million in net inflows. No spot Bitcoin ETF posted net outflows on the day. Bitcoin ETFs recorded five straight weeks of net outflows through Feb. 20, with more than $3.8 billion leaving the funds. Other crypto ETFs also saw inflows on Wednesday. Bitcoin ETFs See Biggest Inflow Day in Three Weeks. Bitcoin ETFs See Biggest Inflow Day in Three Weeks.",
